long_desc.thetext:
Hello,

Changing "overflow" property of ClientDocument to "auto", "scroll", "scrollX", "scrollY" does not lead to displaying of scrollbars in Firefox 2.0.0.7.

Code snippet:

var doc = qx.ui.core.ClientDocument.getInstance();
doc.setOverflow("auto");
//doc.setOverflow("scroll");
//doc.setOverflow("scrollX");
//doc.setOverflow("scrollY");
var lbl = new qx.ui.basic.Label("Label");
lbl.set({
    left : 4000,
    top : 4000,
    width : "auto",
    height : "auto"
});
lbl.addToDocument();


Best regards,
Denis aka Dioc

Note for developers:
this CSS code will be generated
html, body {
  overflow:hidden;
}
By removing this erroneous property the scrollbars will appear - as in other browsers.
